# Firebase Cloud Messaging Configuration
# Choose ONE of the following options:

# Option 1: Service Account File Path (Recommended for Development)
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_PATH=/path/to/firebase-service-account.json

# Option 2: Individual Environment Variables (Recommended for Production)
# FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
# FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=firebase-adminsdk-xxxxx@your-project-id.iam.gserviceaccount.com
# FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYour-Private-Key-Here\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"

# Legacy FCM Server Key (Fallback - Optional)
# FCM_SERVER_KEY=AAAA...your-legacy-server-key

# Note: If Firebase Admin SDK is not configured, the service will fall back to the legacy HTTP API
# if FCM_SERVER_KEY is provided. Otherwise, push notifications will be disabled.
